</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="734" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="106.[179,1389,1356,2768]" pageId="106" pageNumber="734">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,534,2266,2295]" pageId="106" pageNumber="734">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix I. Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Chamba Sacred Languris listed on Schedule II, Part I of the Indian Wildlife (Protection) Act, 1972, amended up to 2002. Occurring in a single restricted locality, it 1s also recognized under the Alliance for Zero Extinction (AZE), as an AZE Species, attracting specific and urgent measures forits conservation. Population estimates indicate only 250 mature adults and less than 500 individuals confined to the narrow Chamba Valley in Himachal Pradesh. Some of the imminent threats confronting the Chamba Sacred Langur include habitat loss, retaliatory killing due to crop raiding, persecution, hunting, logging, expansion of commercial horticulture, and change in land use and other development activities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
